The paper discusses a new analysis for verifying data structures, which involves inferring loop invariants using a combination of decision procedures and an interactive theorem prover. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with program analysis and verification, which could also place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses techniques for reducing annotations and running time, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the verification of complex properties, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
